Blanche Titje
desc: A fresh and inviting flavour.Beautiful and constant head.A cloudy appearance. The nose is more variegated and fresh than the taste. A light spicy note, contains Orange peel as well as coriander to give it its thirst quenching properties.

name: Erdinger
desc: Medium gold colour, with lots of swirling yeast haze in the glass. The nose is really quite clean, crisp and citrussy, with a little hint of yeastiness and grass, but rather neutral overall. On the palate the texture is creamy and dense, and this is a very smooth, sleek, tasty beer that is nevertheles a touch non-descript.

name: Lychee Beer
desc: Pale gold colour with strong notes of lychee on the nose.Beautifully perfumed with fresh lychee.Sweet but not overly cloying.Fantastic drink with strong appeal for cocktail drinkers.Beer for any day, any time. Great with desserts & friends…

name: Heineken
desc: Moderate maltiness with a hint of European hop character and a whiff of what one beer writer calls

name: Honeydew Melon Beer
desc: Hints of ripe honeydew on the nose, with flavours bursting on your palate with every sip. Great drink for a hot & sunny Singapore!

name: Pauwel Kwak
desc: Possesses a deep bright amber color and dense creamy head.Fruity and malty aroma with a slightly spicy character and perhaps also a whiff of pineapple or mango in the background. On the palate it has a very mellow fruity attack, a nougat like solidity.

name: Saison Silly
desc: Saison ales are traditionally brewed in winter to be consumed in the summer months. Pours a brilliant amber with a very slight haze and a thick white head. Nose held an intense fresh strawberry jam of esters. Fairly thin and sweet in the mouth.A very drinkable beer.

name: Konig Ludwig
desc: Pours a hazy straw color forming a very fluffy large head. The aroma features cloves, citrus, bananas and yeast. The taste is exceptionally creamy and smooth with a dry finish. Nice and crisp on the tongue.

name: Tripel Karmeliet
desc: Very refined and complex golden to bronze brew with a fantastic creamy head. It is refine and complex with hints of vanilla mixed with citrus fruits on the nose. Tastes of fresh wheat, but also encompasses the creaminess of oats, together with spicy lemony dryness.

name: Pierre Jean Colombard Chardonnay - Glass
desc: southernfrance, 2011 - this wine has aromas of ripe apple and pears contributing a hint of tropical fruit. mineral and slightly herbaceous notes can also be detected. fresh uncomplicated fruit fill the palate with a tangy, citrusy crisp finish and lively acidity.

name: Pierre Jean Colombard Chardonnay - Bottle
desc: southernfrance, 2011 - this wine has aromas of ripe apple and pears contributing a hint of tropical fruit. mineral and slightly herbaceous notes can also be detected. fresh uncomplicated fruit fill the palate with a tangy, citrusy crisp finish and lively acidity.

name: Frankland Rocky Gully Riesling
desc: frankland river, western australia, 2010 - light in texture but dense with character, offering mineral-tingled apple and quince flavour that remains well modulated through the long, refined finish.

name: Santa Rita Medalla Real Chardonnay
desc: casablancavalley,chile, 2007 - Yellow-green colour with medium-bodied with tones of tropical fruits, hazelnut and notes of honey.a tasteful wine with good acidity, complex structure, sweetness and persistence.

name: Morton Estate White Label Sauvignon Blanc
desc: marlborough, new zealand,2011 - Ripe, lifted peaches, limes and a fuller bodied palate. An excellent example of a marlborough Sauvignon Blanc.

name: De Bortoli Family selection Shiraz Cabernet - Glass
desc: bilbul vineyards, australia, 2010/11 - vibrant purple in colour with crimson hues with lifted plum and berry aromas. on the palate, it has an intense plum and spice characters with rounded fresh fruit flavours, soft tannins and light toasty oak.

name: De Bortoli Family selection Shiraz Cabernet - Bottle
desc: bilbul vineyards, australia, 2010/11 - vibrant purple in colour with crimson hues with lifted plum and berry aromas. on the palate, it has an intense plum and spice characters with rounded fresh fruit flavours, soft tannins and light toasty oak.

name: Mitolo Jester Shiraz
desc: mclarenvale,australia, 2007/08 - Bright ruby, dense, rather backward aromas of cassis, bitter cherry and black pepper, with hints of anise and clove.  Flavours of sweet, dark berries, tobacco and roasted coffee with long finish.

name: De Bortoli Windy Peak Pinot Noir
desc: victoria, Australia, 2009/10 - medium red in colour with purple hue coupled with a complex cherry-like pinot fruit aroma. the palate shows good concentration with strong strawberry/spice flavours and hints of maceration.

name: Montes Classic Merlot
desc: colchagua valley, chile,2009/10 - tasty, with briary tannins carrying good black cherry and blackberry fruit notes. shows a touch of toast on the finish.

name: Tasca D'Almerita Regaliali Nero D'Avola
desc: sicilia, italy, 2009 - bright, intense ruby red, cherry, mulberry, sour black cherry, blueberry, vanilla, sage. pleasantlyvelvety and well balanced tannins.

name: ToressellaProsecco Brut
desc: valdobbiadene, italy, nv - A semi-sparkling wine with a distinctive varietal style: its bouquet displays the grape's characteristic aromatic note and the palate is fresh and appealing.
